Command Options
 'connectionSpec' is one of:
 (a) '--work-dir workDirectory' : The path to the work directory that is used by an independent integration server.
 (b) '--ext-vault-dir' : The path to the directory which contains the external directory vault.
                         Not for use with --set-as-default option.
 (c) '--admin-host (-i) <host> --admin-port (-p) <port> [[--https [--cacert <cacertFile> [--cacert-password <cacertPassword>] | --insecure]] | --no-https]'
                      : Hostname/ipAddress and port of a remote integration node or independent integration server.
                        HTTPS options are required if making a connection to an integration node or server that has SSL enabled for REST administration.
                        If neither https nor no-https is specified, the connection is tried first with https and then falls back no-https.
                        If no cacert file is provided and default admin-ssl is enabled, the cacert file defaults to the admin-ssl default pem file.
 (d) '--admin-host (-i) <uri> [--cacert <cacertFile> [--cacert-password <cacertPassword>] | --insecure]'
                      : URI for the remote integration node or independent integration server in the form tcp://[<user>[:<password>]@]<host>:<port> or ssl://[<user>[:<password>]@]<host>:<port> 'integrationNodeName' optional for validation.
                        If a user name and password are supplied, any URI Reserved characters in the password must be percent-encoded.
 (e) '--integration-connection-file (-n) fileName' : File containing connection parameters for an integration node or independent integration server.
 (f) 'integrationNodeName' : Name of a locally defined integration node.
 '--https' use HTTPS for the connection to the integration node or server.
 '--no-https' do not use HTTPS for the connection to the integration node or server.
 '--cacert <cacertFile>' path to the certificate file in either PEM, P12, or JKS format to verify the integration node or server.
 '--cacert-password <cacertPassword>' the password for password-protected cacert files.
 '--insecure' do not verify the certificate returned by the integration node or server.
 '--create' indicates the credential will be created in the vault.
 '--update' indicates an existing credential will be updated in the vault.
 '--delete' indicates an existing credential will be deleted from the vault.
 '--report' indicates that reportable details of an existing credential will be described.
 '--export' export the selected credential(s) from the vault into a zip archive file.
 '--import' import the selected credential(s) from a zip archive file into the vault.
 '--set-as-default' indicates that an existing credential will be set as the default to be used for that credential type.
 '--vault-key <arg>' indicates the vault key to be used to access the vault where the credential is stored.
 '--ext-vault-key <arg>' indicates the vault key to be used to access the external directory vault where the credential is stored.
 '--vaultrc-location <arg>' indicates the location of the .mqsivaultrc file.
 '--credential-type <arg>' indicates the type of the credential. See table below for the list of credential types and their properties.
 '--credential-name <arg>' indicates the name of the credential.
 '--integration-server (-e) server' integration server name
 '--all-integration-servers' indicates all integration servers
 '--auth-type <arg>' indicates the authentication type of the credential.
                     This options can be omitted except when updating a credential to a different authentication type.
                     When updating a credential to a different authentication type all properties for the new authentication type must be specified.
 '--archive-location' location of the zip archive file to be imported-from/exported-to.
 '--archive-key' The archive key used to protect the records in the archive.
 '--trace traceFileName' send verbose internal trace to the specified file.

